    <monsterdescription>
      <p>FIXME: darkness</p>
      <p>
	The phage are a hive mind Ee’die, a colony or genet, composed of a dozens of
	individuals, known as ramets, whose minds are linked.	Each Phage-Genet acts as
	a single individual, the death of any individual Phage-Ramet is a matter of
	mild annoyance to a Phage, though certainly a sacrifice the Phage is willing to
	make to achieve its goals.
      </p>

      <p>
	An individual adult phage-ramet is the size of a small dog and has features
	that resemble a grub or arthropod, a hard exoskeleton covers their heads and
	thorax, while their abdomens are soft and vulnerable.  Tufts of needle like
	hair sprout from their bodies.  Phage-ramets have a lamprey-like, cyclostamatic
	mouth which they use to attach to the back of the necks of their prey.  Once
	attached they are able to control the behaviour of their hosts using a mind
	tether.  They are almost always invisble and hard to detect.  Once seen however,
	they are not unsee.
      </p>

